  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Gatumba Rukaramu Flood Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Since April 2021, Lake Tanganyika has been gradually rising affecting families living along the shores of the lake. OCHA report of  25th May, reports that over 45,000 indivudals were affected and out of this over 24,000 were displaced and relocate to other areas. The humanitarian actors were responding to this crises when suddently on 13th and 14th of January Rusizi and Kajeke rivers burst its bank and flooded two zones of Bujumbura Rural, namely Rukaramu and Gatumba zones. The flooding displaced over 5,152 families at total of 27,760 individuals (fews net report 18th May) . This came at time the Government and other actors were planning to resettle about 8,712 affected from the 2020 floods.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support   the IDP of Sobel  with  NFIs  and Shelter</narrative>
  </description>
